def: In an inverted posture; with the top or head downward; upsidedown; as, to turn a carriage topsy-turvy.
A foreboding; an omen. [Obs.] "Abodements must not now affrightus." Shak.
A kind of pad worn on the leg under the boot. [Obs.] Nares.
Spontaneous; voluntary. [Obs.] Jer. Taylor.-- Ul*tro"ne*ous*ly, adv. [Obs.] -- Ul*tro"ne*ous*ness, n. [Obs.]
One who, or that which, gives or adds strength. Sir W. Temple.
The act or process of paralyzing, or the state of beingparalyzed.
A collective name for the Indians of Nicaragua and Honduras.
An instrument for measuring or registering the amount ofcloudiness.
